line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Of course, neither of these men are so naive as=
 to believe that
print alone will safeguard their businesses. These are brilliant guys, afte=
r all. Two decades ago, when Thompson was serving as Remnick=E2=80=99s digi=
tal chief, they adapted <em>The New Yorker </em>to Internet 1.0=E2=80=94whi=
ch, as Remnick told me, required dramatic =E2=80=9Cpsychological, editorial=
, and almost physiological=E2=80=9D changes on the part of the staff. =E2=
=80=9CAnybody who tries to predict with any confidence what this business w=
ill look like in 10 years is playing a mug=E2=80=99s game. I don=E2=80=99t =
think it=E2=80=99s possible,=E2=80=9D he said.
Thompson, to his credit, was clear-eyed that, =E2=80=9Cif going from 10 iss=
ues to 12 issues is the most important thing I do, you fire me immediately,=
 right? It=E2=80=99s not our principal strategy.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">Still, it can be unnerving to hear no real answer to the question <em>be=
yond </em>print. Remnick cited the advent of A.I.-generated audio versions =
of the magazine=E2=80=99s stories, while noting, =E2=80=9Cadmittedly, that=
=E2=80=99s certainly not the
be all and end all of A.I. and its future.=E2=80=9D Thompson said he and hi=
s team are putting a lot of effort into other ideas, but most of it seems t=
o be around optimizing the existing business=E2=80=94such as determining wh=
en nonsubscribers should hit the paywall. =E2=80=9CShould you be shown just=
 the first 200 words of the article? Should you be shown 300? Should you be=
 shown 100? Should you be shown quotes? Should you be shown summaries? Shou=
ld you be shown excerpts? A lot of our work is going into testing that.=E2=
=80=9D
(Of course, <em>The Atlantic </em>is probably already doing this sort of te=
sting and learning. At any rate, it can.)</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Coincidentall=
y, on the same day the News/Media Alliance lawsuit was filed and the Nation=
al Magazine Awards nominees were announced, I found myself in an off-the-re=
cord meeting with a high-level executive at one of the major tech companies=
=2E When asked what was occupying his brain space these
days, he said: =E2=80=9CA.I., A.I., A.I., that=E2=80=99s one, two, and thre=
e.=E2=80=9D Like everyone in his field, he evidenced total clarity about th=
e fact that the new technology would fundamentally change, well, <em>everyt=
hing</em>, and that we were only in the earliest, Motorola DynaTAC 8000X ph=
ase of its evolution. I have no doubt that Thompson, Remnick, and their con=
temporaries across the publishing industry have countenanced that fact, but=
 it=E2=80=99s not clear that they have any real plan for what to do about
it.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>Anyway, for whatever it=E2=80=99s =
worth, both <em>The New Yorker </em>and <em>New York</em> led the Ellie nom=
inations this year, with seven apiece. This included nods in the highly cov=
eted =E2=80=9Cgeneral excellence=E2=80=9D category, a distinction they shar=
ed with <em>National Geographic</em>, ProPublica, and The Verge. <em>The At=
lantic </em>picked up four nominations, one for reporting, two for photogra=
phy, and one for
<a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktx=
clJLZ0dWQjFXZmU1MVdUYVdTcWhkRWh5ST0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW5=
0aWMuY29tL2ZhbWlseS9hcmNoaXZlLzIwMjQvMDcvZ2FtYmxpbmctZXZlcnl3aGVyZS1waG9uZS=
1hZGRpY3Rpb24vNjc4OTEzLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249SW4rdGhlK1Jvb20rLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSU=
yslMjgyJTJGMTQlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PUluK1RoZStSb29tKy0rU1VCU0NS=
SUJFUlMrJTI4MiUyRjE0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDA=
yNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMm=
EiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwODU1NjF9/9cae=
8b37a689a69d678182c27416b5b1cab40d68d304bc6b5f5b311c477ca06f" style=3D"text=
